AUC

To quantify the total bacterial growth over time, we calculate the total area under the curve. This is done with the function auc(). Before that, negative values for density increase were filtered out (i.e., strains or replicates that didnt grow). For comparison between treatments, the total AUC (calculated using density increase) and AUC_raw (calculated using raw density) is normalized with the AUC of the strain grown in the control treatment (no chemicals added, just normal growth media with DMSO).
